The paper deals with the problem of compressive phase retrieval, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions numerical simulations, which suggests that it may fall under computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the sparsity level and dimension of the input signal, which are concepts commonly used in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for recovering a jointly sparse and low-rank matrix, which could potentially fall under the category of scientific computing (cs.SI).
